headline.main: JAPAN HELD UNABLE TO FACE 'ALL OF US'; Sir Keith Murdoch Says Nation Will Not Defy Democracies

lead_paragraph: Declaring that Japan would never be "strong enough to face us all," Sir Keith Murdoch, Australian newspaper publisher and former Director General of Information in Australia, expressed the belief yesterday that Japan would not try to press its policy or expansion in the face of a united front of the democracies.
abstract: Sir K Murdoch on Australian effort
